getSupplyRate

nodes.documentation:
@notice Calculates the Dai savings rate per block
@return The Dai savings rate per block (as a percentage, and scaled by 1e18)
nodes.name: dsrPerBlock

nodes.documentation: @notice Resets the baseRate and multiplier per block based on the stability fee and Dai savings rate
nodes.name: poke

attributes.name: DAIInterestRateModelV2
getSupplyRate

attributes.documentation:
@notice Calculates the Dai savings rate per block
@return The Dai savings rate per block (as a percentage, and scaled by 1e18)
attributes.name: dsrPerBlock

attributes.documentation: @notice Resets the baseRate and multiplier per block based on the stability fee and Dai savings rate
attributes.name: poke

params.jug_: The address of the Dai jug (where SF is kept)
params.jumpMultiplierPerYear: The multiplierPerBlock after hitting a specified utilization point
params.kink_: The utilization point at which the jump multiplier is applied
params.pot_: The address of the Dai pot (where DSR is earned)

dsrPerBlock().return: The Dai savings rate per block (as a percentage, and scaled by 1e18)

params.borrows: The amount of borrows in the market
params.cash: The amount of cash in the market
params.reserves: The amount of reserves in the market

getBorrowRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).return: The borrow rate percentage per block as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)

params.borrows: The total amount of borrows the market has outstanding
params.cash: The total amount of cash the market has
params.reserveFactorMantissa: The current reserve factor the market has
params.reserves: The total amnount of reserves the market has

getSupplyRate(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.return: The supply rate per block (as a percentage, and scaled by 1e18)

params.borrows: The amount of borrows in the market
params.cash: The amount of cash in the market
params.reserves: The amount of reserves in the market (currently unused)

utilizationRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).return: The utilization rate as a mantissa between [0, 1e18]

dsrPerBlock().notice: Calculates the Dai savings rate per block

getBorrowRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the current borrow rate per block, with the error code expected by the market

getSupplyRate(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Calculates the current supply interest rate per block including the Dai savings rate

poke().notice: Resets the baseRate and multiplier per block based on the stability fee and Dai savings rate

utilizationRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the utilization rate of the market: `borrows / (cash + borrows - reserves)`

userdoc.notice: The parameterized model described in section 2.4 of the original Btntex Protocol whitepaper. Version 2 modifies the original interest rate model by increasing the "gap" or slope of the model prior to the "kink" from 0.05% to 2% with the goal of "smoothing out" interest rate changes as the utilization rate increases.
